One-shot sentinel: while this file exists AND the GitHub Secret
OWNER_WHATSAPP_NUMBER is set, the deploy deletes ONLY that number's sessions
from ~/.hermes/state.db (DM + group participation), keyed by session_key.

The delete helper backs up the db to state.db.predelete.<size>b first and only
removes rows matching that number, so everyone else's data (e.g. the friend's)
is untouched. Guarded by the on-VM marker ~/.hermes/.owner_sessions_deleted so
it runs at most once.

Dormant until the secret is set. Remove this file (and clear the secret) once
the delete has run.
